{{Merge from|Armed resistance in Chile (1973–1990)|discuss=Talk:Chilean Resistance#Merge|date=March 2018}}
'''Chilean Resistance''' is the collective term used to refer to a broad range of activities initiated by [[cultural]], [[social]] and [[political]] organisations in opposition to the [[Pinochet regime]] between 1973 and 1990.<ref>"Chile Rising: Women in the Resistance - Chilean women fought for a democratic government under Allende, against the fascist dictator Pinochet and now demand peace and economic justice." by [[Gladys Marin]]. ''[[Political Affairs]]'' v. 82, no. 7, (2003)</ref><ref>''Women in the Chilean resistance : two members of the MIR (Movement of the Revolutionary Left) speak of their experiences as political prisoners and active members of the resistance ''by Gladys Díaz; Carmen Castillo OCLC 6233253</ref> Among the publications from this movement are the ''Chilean Resistance Courier'' <ref>[http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/5031175&referer=brief_results OCLC record].</ref> and ''Human Rights for Chile'' published by the Support Committee for Chilean Resistance.<ref>[http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/221275250&referer=brief_results OCLC record]</ref>

The movement has further led to a number of works in various media.<ref>[https://journals.ku.edu/index.php/latr/article/view/1287/1262] Latin American Theater Review 1999,p.204-  Lepeley, Osear, "The Cueca of the Last Judgment: Politics of Chilean. Resistance in Tres Marías y una Rosa"</ref><ref>Karaxu : the music of the Chilean Resistance; an analysis of composition and performance 	J Fairley 1987.</ref>

